headline: MarketAxess (MKTX) Loses -9.63% in 4 Weeks, Here's Why a Trend Reversal May be Around the Corner
summary: MarketAxess (MKTX) has become technically an oversold stock now, which implies exhaustion of the heavy selling pressure on it. This, combined with strong agreement among Wall Street analysts in revising earnings estimates higher, indicates a potential trend reversal for the stock in the near term.

headline: MarketAxess Expands AI-Powered Pricing Engine to Cover Municipal Bonds
summary: NEW YORK, December 05, 2024--MarketAxess Holdings Inc. (Nasdaq: MKTX), the operator of a leading electronic trading platform for fixed-income securities, today announced that CP+, the AI-powered, algorithmic pricing engine for global credit and rates markets, will now also cover municipal bonds.
